Author: TOM47
Title: [ANN][ICO] Monoreto - A New Generation Social Network
Body: Chef Day with Monoreto https://medium.com/@monoretoinc/chef-day-with-monoreto-3914f441e9f5 Did you miss International Chef Day? Maybe you noticed an uptick in the number of food photos on popular social networks like Instagram. There’s nothing like photos of other people’s food, right? From take-out to home-cooked culinary delights, Instagram is full of food even when it’s not an international holiday for chefs! Granny’s cookies, your sister’s rump roast, the restaurants with their fancy plates — it’s enough to send you running to the refrigerator for a snack! But there’s more to life than posts about food, even on a food holiday. We love seeing the familiar faces of loved ones, exotic places others are visiting, décor and artwork, and more in our photo feeds, and we love taking those pictures, too! But here’s your chance to get into the swing of things with all things food, even though you missed the holiday, itself. Publish your thematic pictures of food on Monoreto — those with some artistic quality and beauty all their own — and you may earn an extra 1,000 tokens for your post! That’s right, the top five thematic food photos will get 1,000 tokens. So, take your best shot of your yummies delights, whether you’re the super chef or not!

Author: fishervwb
Title: [ANN][ICO] Monoreto - A New Generation Social Network
Body: Monoreto Business Development Crew On Tour: News from Asia https://medium.com/@monoretoinc/monoreto-business-development-crew-on-tour-news-from-asia-3905ae32729c  Our COO Alexandra Matveeva and our CBDO Zakhar Burmakov started their Asian road show — the series of business meet-ups in China and Singapore. Within the framework of the roadshow they will talk to local start-up angels and venture investors. But the first days of trip is dedicated to the participation in outstanding fin-tech events these countries are known for.  Tomorrow they will join the NIFTY Hackathon and Conference. This magnificent event is dedicated to blockchain gaming and decentralized applications, Coinbase and 0x platforms sent their speakers to the sessions of this forum. Non-Fungible Tokens, Lightning and Raiden Infrastructure problems will be discussed with the leading professionals of the sphere.  On July 26 our business developers will join the Blockchain Summit in Hong Kong. Monoreto platform is the Silver Partner of this event organized by UNICOM — this is a sign of great acknowledgement in the industry. Our guys will present the stand of Monoreto and speak about our project with the guests.  The rest of the road show will be spent in Shanghai and Singapore. Alexandra and Zakhar will have a meetings with the Korean and Chinese investors highly interested in the investment in Monoreto platform.

Author: gerymakgyaer
Title: [ANN][ICO] Monoreto - A New Generation Social Network
Body: One of the key components of the Monoreto social network is the MON token. This is the internal currency of the social network. Each MON token is worth the equivalent of 5 U.S. cents. Tokens are used to give likes to posts and reward users that post quality content to the network. In using tokens to give these likes, users that give them are also pushed up in the newsfeed alongside the accounts that are earning the likes.  Likes aren’t restricted to single tokens. If a user really likes a particular post, he will be able to hand over more tokens along with his like. It’s kind of a way to say thank you for something that is reinforcing the reason why people want to use social networks and showing appreciation for quality content. Transactions with MON tokens will all be made using special wallets that are tied to personal user accounts. Conversion of MON tokens to major cryptocurrencies and vice versa will all be possible in this wallet.  MON tokens are a great investment tool. Users are able to use them to support and promote projects and companies that they feel a connection with. Investing in companies will no longer require lengthy bureaucracy. Instead, investment can be made as easy as liking a project. Over time, a percentage of the earnings of new content creators will go back to the investors. The incentives for investment are great.  Monoreto will also feature online quizzes for its users. Winners will be awarded MON token prizes. These tokens can then be put to use as the user sees fit.  MON tokens can also be donated to charitable causes. Again, making a donation is as simple as liking a post. What’s more, the simplicity and transparency of this operation are a lot less off-putting than having to make a bank transfer.  https://www.facebook.com/monoreto/photos/a.571323913237768.1073741828.569153790121447/583749701995189/?type=3&theater

Title: [ANN][ICO] Monoreto - A New Generation Social Network
Body: What is your special things of your project?

Author: Monoreto.Com
Title: [ANN][ICO] Monoreto - A New Generation Social Network
Body: Hello! Thanks for your question! It is quite difficult to answer it in several words, we devoted the whole Whitepaper to it:)  However, we consider the two main issues as our biggest advantages. They are as follows: the motivation to put likes and the user cases of the platform.  If we want such a social network to work, we should create mechanisms that will make liking (and giving a small amount of money - 5 cents) profitable and useful for both sides. Other projects often lack such mechanisms.  So, why would you like someone's photos and videos, spend tokens in Monoreto?  - when you put likes, you also promote your own account in the newsfeed (along with accounts, that receive many likes) - if you put many likes, you can get a part of Monoreto's weekly profit (do not confuse it with making profit by just holding tokens, they are NOT securities) - by liking photos, you participate in forecast competitions.
